<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>When commenting lines in yaml-config, comments can be started only from 0-position of string, to be processed correctly (to be ignored). Otherwise, by yaml-specification, comment can be started from any position of string, and text after comment should be ignored.</p>

<p>The patch is only replace 
{quote}
if ($line[0] == '#') {
  // comment
  continue;
}
{quote} 
in Zend_Config_Yaml to 
{quote}
$line = rtrim(preg_replace("/#.*$/", "", $line));
{quote}</p>

    </div>
